    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-lab-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 ASME V&V 40 factors for MRL 2 and determined that the evidence base supports acceptance of the CFD model for the stated COU. Seven factors were formally assessed; six were scoped as not-assessed consistent with MRL 2 requirements. All assessed factors were judged to meet or exceed required levels, and the overall assurance level is declared Medium, consistent with the Class II device classification, Medium model influence, and High decision consequence. The validation activities cover the full operating envelope and use the clinical QoI directly. The assessment team is satisfied that the model is fit for purpose for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions.",
